lations with M$_\\ast$\nor SFR, and only a marginally significant dependence (at $\\sim 2\\sigma$) on\nmorphology-related parameters, with slightly higher velocities in galaxies of\nsmaller size (probed by the equivalent radius), higher concentration, and\nhigher SFR surface density. The outflows are consistent with models of\naccelerating, momentum-driven winds, with densities decreasing towards the\noutskirts. Our moderately lower ISM velocities compared to those found in\nsimilar studies at lower redshifts suggest that inflows and internal turbulence\nmight play an increased role at $z>2$. We estimate mass outflow rates\ncomparable to the SFRs of the galaxies, and an average escape velocity of 625\nkm/s, suggesting that most of the ISM will remain bound to the galaxy halo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jun 2022 21:14:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Aug 2022 22:13:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-16"}
